node.title: Protesters block road at Auckland's northern boundary
node.description: Protestors gathered around the northern side of Auckland's northern boundary this morning, blocking the road.
node.content:
["Protestors gathered around the northern side of Auckland's northern boundary this morning, blocking the road.", "", "
Protesters blocked the main northern border checkpoint on State Highway 1. Photo: Te Rūnanga ō Ngāti Whātua
", "The main northern border checkpoint on State Highway 1 was blocked for a considerable period of time, police said.", "Te Rūnanga ō Ngāti Whātua released a statement saying southbound traffic had to be diverted due to protestors blocking the highway with their vehicles.", "Te Rūnanga ō Ngāti Whātua uri and chief operating officer Antony Thompson said trucks carrying food and medical supplies were being held up unnecessarily "creating major risks to our communities and whānau of the North".", "He said thoughtless moves like this put whānau in danger and urged members of these groups to think about the impact they were having on those they believed they were trying to protect", "Thompson said protesters were using this as an opportunity to "grandstand their issue".", "", "
Police attended the protest and cars were towed away. Photo: Te Rūnanga ō Ngāti Whātua
", "Vehicles were towed and traffic is now moving.", "Police said they worked to ensure lanes were open at the checkpoint so members of the public undertaking lawful travel across the boundary can do so safely."]
